 Nigeria’s President Muhammadu Buhari on Wednesday presided over the ninth virtual meeting of the Federal Executive Council (FEC) at the State House, Abuja. The News Agency of Nigeria (NAN) reports that those in attendance include Vice President Yemi Osinbajo; Secretary to the Government of the Federation, Boss Mustapha; Chief of Staff to the President, Prof. Ibrahim Gambari Others are the Head of Service of the Federation, Mrs Folashade Yemi-Esan and Alhaji Lai Mohammed (Information and Culture) as well as The Ministers, who are expected to make presentations at the meeting, include Attorney-General and Minister of Justice, Abubakar Malami; Mr Chukwuemeka Nwajiuba, Minister of State for Education; Zainab Ahmed, Ministry of Finance, Budget and National Planning; Ra’uf Aregbesola, Interior The other ministers also physically attending the meeting at the Council Chambers include the Minister of Sports and Youth Development, Mr Sunday Dare and that of Works and Housing, Babatunde Fashola. NAN reports that a minute’s silence was observed in honour of late Isma’ila Isa Funtua, onetime Minister of Water Resources (1983) during the defunct Shagari administration. Funtua died of cardiac arrest on July 20(NAN)